    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - New Vehicle Processing Manual - NEW TRUCK RECEIVING AND
        DAMAGE CLAIM PROCESSING - FILLING OUT THE DELIVERY RECEIPT (501)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="4">
        <title>FILLING OUT THE DELIVERY RECEIPT (501)</title>
        <para>The Receipt is designed for inspecting the vehicle in clockwise direction, starting at vehicle front.
            Record damage and shortage(s) using the 5-digit damage code system, illustrated in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1000510">Figure 9</hotlnk>
            and in the following example:
        </para>
        <seqlist style="alphalc">
            <item>
                <para>The 1st and 2nd digits are DAMAGE AREA CODE indicating the area of damage: "78" = VISOR, EXTERIOR
                    SUN.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The 3rd and 4th digits are DAMAGE TYPE CODE indicating the type of damage: "12" = SCRATCHED. (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1000512">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The 5th digit is DAMAGE SEVERITY CODE indicating the severity of damage: "3" = 3 to 6 inches
                </para>
                <para>LENGTH OR DIAMETER. (See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1000512">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>THE EXAMPLE ABOVE indicates a 6-inch long scratch on the exterior sun visor by using 5-digit code
            78-12-3.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1000510" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000510.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" resolution="300"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Damage Area Codes</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>OTHER EXAMPLES of proper damage coding, are shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1000511">Figure 10</hotlnk>, and the following examples:
        </para>
        <para>Windshield broken: 20-21-0</para>
        <para>Bumper bent severely: 03-01-6</para>
        <para>Light cable missing: 47-08-0</para>
        <figure id="f1000511" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000511.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="300"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Damage Area Codes</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1000512" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000512.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="152px" resolution="300"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Damage and Severity Codes</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>IN THE EVENT of multiple damages to the same coding area, enter a 5-digit damage code for each instance of
            damage in the blank 5-digit spaces (D,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1000513">Figure 12</hotlnk>), or written into Dealer Remarks (E,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1000513">Figure 12</hotlnk>). Report damage that is not covered by the standard damage
            codes in the blank coding section and/or the Dealer's Remarks sections.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1000513" figsize="full-pg">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000513.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="592px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Form 501</caption>
        </figure>
